<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="260" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,356,382]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Description.</emphasis>
Penis in side view very wide, usually with even dorsal and ventral margins (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 94–117" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[229,1355,193,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-32@11.[222,1366,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 94–117. Male genitalia. 94–103―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) karakolensis, 104–105―A. (A.) perarmata, 106–117―A. (A.) laevis. 94–98, 102, 104, 106, 108, 110, 112, 114, 116―penis, lateral view, 99–101, 103, 105, 107, 109, 111, 113, 115, 117―male anal collar appendage. 102–103―after Dubovsky (1984), 104–105―after Dlabola (1958), 106–107―af- ter Ribaut (1952)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398496/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Figs. 106, 110, 112, 114, 116</figureCitation>
). Occasionally, dorsal margin slightly uneven, with few small denticles in middle part (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1301,392,419]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–117" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[229,1355,193,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-32@11.[222,1366,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 94–117. Male genitalia. 94–103―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) karakolensis, 104–105―A. (A.) perarmata, 106–117―A. (A.) laevis. 94–98, 102, 104, 106, 108, 110, 112, 114, 116―penis, lateral view, 99–101, 103, 105, 107, 109, 111, 113, 115, 117―male anal collar appendage. 102–103―after Dubovsky (1984), 104–105―after Dlabola (1958), 106–107―af- ter Ribaut (1952)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398496/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
). Male anal collar appendage wide, asymmetrically expanded, with angular protrusion on dorsal margin and with pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,544,464,491]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–117" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[229,1355,193,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-32@11.[222,1366,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 94–117. Male genitalia. 94–103―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) karakolensis, 104–105―A. (A.) perarmata, 106–117―A. (A.) laevis. 94–98, 102, 104, 106, 108, 110, 112, 114, 116―penis, lateral view, 99–101, 103, 105, 107, 109, 111, 113, 115, 117―male anal collar appendage. 102–103―after Dubovsky (1984), 104–105―after Dlabola (1958), 106–107―af- ter Ribaut (1952)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398496/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Figs. 107, 109, 111, 113, 115, 117</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="260" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,500,526]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Biology.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[333,462,501,527]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
it was collected in a wet meadow on the riverbank and on an irrigated plot overgrown with alfalfa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" box="[199,1101,572,599]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,572,598]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Calling signal.</emphasis>
Signals of males from the following localities were investigated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014906328" collectingDate="2009-07-16" country="Kyrgyzstan" county="Arkyt Village" location="West Tien Shan" municipality="Eastern" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" specimenCount="1">
1. 
<collectingCountry box="[227,358,609,635]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:76154D29AE55CF36FF79FF43FE6BFC05:FB63AAE4AE55CF36FE9EFDB5FD96FDC1" box="[368,545,608,635]" country="Kyrgyzstan" county="Arkyt Village" municipality="Eastern" name="West Tien Shan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">West Tien Shan</location>
, 
<collectingMunicipality box="[555,639,609,635]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Eastern</collectingMunicipality>
part of Chatkal Mtn. Range, environs of 
<collectingCounty box="[1095,1250,608,634]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Arkyt Village</collectingCounty>
, wet meadow on riverbank, 
<date box="[272,426,644,671]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" value="2009-07-16">
<collectingDate box="[272,426,644,671]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" value="2009-07-16">16. VII. 2009</collectingDate>
</date>
, signals of one male recorded at 22–23 
<superScript attach="right" box="[870,900,644,671]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">oC</superScript>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014906325" collectingDate="2016-06-27" country="Kyrgyzstan" location="Batken Oblast" municipality="Tortkul' Reservoir" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" specimenCount="1">
2. 
<collectingCountry box="[226,357,681,707]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:76154D29AE55CF36FF79FF43FE6BFC05:FB63AAE4AE55CF36FE81FD7CFDA6FD79" box="[367,529,680,706]" country="Kyrgyzstan" municipality="Tortkul' Reservoir" name="Batken Oblast" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Batken Oblast</location>
, the shore of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[674,878,680,706]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Tortkul’ Reservoir</collectingMunicipality>
ca. 
<locationDeviation box="[921,1243,680,707]" location="South-West of Batken" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<quantity box="[921,991,680,707]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
South-West of Batken
</locationDeviation>
, alfalfa in apricot garden, 
<date box="[241,385,716,743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" value="2016-06-27">
<collectingDate box="[241,385,716,743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" value="2016-06-27">27. VI. 2016</collectingDate>
</date>
, signals of one male recorded at 30 
<superScript attach="right" box="[787,818,716,743]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">oC</superScript>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
In general, the calling signal structure is approximately the same as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Tishechkin" authorityYear="2017" box="[972,1128,753,779]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venosa" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
<emphasis box="[972,996,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1011,1028,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1050,1128,753,778]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1179,1204,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">A.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dlabola" authorityYear="1967" box="[1209,1366,752,779]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalchica" subGenus="Anaceratagallia">
(
<emphasis box="[1218,1235,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1257,1366,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">chalchica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 118–133" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[273,1316,188,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-16@12.[266,1320,181,1763]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 118–133. Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) spp., calling signal oscillograms. 118–123―A. (A.) laevis, 124–133― A. (A.) camphorosmatis. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “121–123” and “129–133”are given under the same numbers. 118–119, 121–122―male from West Tien Shan, locality No. 1 in the list in calling signal description, 120, 123―male from Batken Oblast, ibid., locality No. 2, 124, 129―male from Saratov Oblast, ibid., locality No. 1, 125, 130―male from Kaskelen River, Southern Kazakhstan, ibid., locality No. 3, 126, 131―male from Zhansagurov, South-eastern Kazakhstan, steppe, ibid., locality No. 9, 127, 132―same locality, male from wet meadow on the riverbank, 128, 133―male from Toktogul Reservoir, Kyrgyzstan, ibid., locality No. 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398498/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Figs. 118–120</figureCitation>
), but the temporal pattern of the second part is different (
<figureCitation box="[904,1072,788,815]" captionStart="FIGURES 118–133" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[273,1316,188,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-16@12.[266,1320,181,1763]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 118–133. Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) spp., calling signal oscillograms. 118–123―A. (A.) laevis, 124–133― A. (A.) camphorosmatis. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “121–123” and “129–133”are given under the same numbers. 118–119, 121–122―male from West Tien Shan, locality No. 1 in the list in calling signal description, 120, 123―male from Batken Oblast, ibid., locality No. 2, 124, 129―male from Saratov Oblast, ibid., locality No. 1, 125, 130―male from Kaskelen River, Southern Kazakhstan, ibid., locality No. 3, 126, 131―male from Zhansagurov, South-eastern Kazakhstan, steppe, ibid., locality No. 9, 127, 132―same locality, male from wet meadow on the riverbank, 128, 133―male from Toktogul Reservoir, Kyrgyzstan, ibid., locality No. 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398498/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Figs. 121–123</figureCitation>
). Syllables in the second part of signal follow each other at a rate of 8–9/s at a temperature 22–23 
<superScript attach="right" box="[886,913,824,851]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">oC</superScript>
and at a rate of 11–12/s at 30 
<superScript attach="right" box="[1250,1280,824,851]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">oC</superScript>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="260" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,356,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,860,886]" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southern half of Europe, Eastern Mediterranean (
<collectingCountry box="[911,978,860,887]" name="Israel" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Israel</collectingCountry>
), southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1243,860,886]" name="Ukraine" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1257,1424,860,887]" country="Ukraine" name="Odesa" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Odessa Oblast</collectingRegion>
), Transcaucasia (
<collectingCountry box="[326,422,896,923]" name="Georgia" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Georgia</collectingCountry>
), Western part of Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[739,870,896,922]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
up to Syrdarya Karatau Mtn. Range, 
<collectingCountry box="[1308,1437,897,923]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
(West Tien Shan), 
<collectingCountry box="[358,472,932,958]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="260">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
